fact number 66:
things ac valhalla does better than ac odyssey
- sound design and general weight behind attacks
- settlement and raiding system
- main story / character development
- actually being an assassins creed game
- general gameplay loop for open world
things ac odyssey does better than ac valhalla
- overall combat
- world aesthetic
- rpg system
- stealth gameplay
- difficulty
- level design

valhalla adds a ton of meaningful new systems that enhance the world but also decided to remove all things good about combat, the rpg system (item collection and whatnot), and general objectives and motivations to play. quite a shame, if they just kept odyssey's core systems but just applied it to the more refined gameplay experience that's been crafted this game would be a 10/10

fact number 99:
Completed two seasonals today 

Tonikaku Kawaii had a really fun and cute premise and the first half of the show has got to be some of the best cutesy fluffiest content I've ever watched. The rest of the show was a little more average, but it gets an 7/10 from me for such a superb start

Majo no Tabitabi is home to one of my favorite protagonists, the traveling Ashen Witch Elaina who I like because she does not give a fuck about anyone and anything. The show is a collection of really fun stories and memorable moments and really succeeds as an episodic adventure. Overall it was a super fun watch, quality show: another 8/10 from me 🙂

fact number 100:
Recently completed My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU and My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU TOO!

The first season gets a 7/10 (great) from me, it had some great comedic moments but in terms of character depth it mostly detailed the MC's cynical and abrasive personality. Overall a great slice of life comedy with a bit of romance and a humorous MC.

However the second season gets a 9/10 (incredible) from me. The first season set up a cast of very interesting but flawed characters and the second season dived into the problems they faced in a very deep and compelling manner. Combined with some great character interactions/slice of life content, it's a show I really enjoyed and thought a lot about 😃 , MC is definitely one of my favorite characters of all time.

Looking forward to the final season :yep:
